,Not Recommended,399790,30713750,Posted: 24 March,all,That Guy ☆VG☆,"Destiny Warriors is a RPG Maker made game whose whole premise is taken almost verbatim off of the manga Naruto, even titles, characters, and events are basically the same. Storyline is bland and the use of vulgarity takes you back to when you were in middle school and started cursing for the first time. Generic, unoriginal soundtrack with a flood of grammatical errors help to unimmerse you from what would be a terrible game to an unplayable game. Battle system is riddled with tediousness and unbalanced scaling, just plain boring with a lot of glitches (ex: where the tooltip for certain abilities would let you attack multiple enemies and only give you one attack). Everytime I tried to take a screenshot or close the game it crashed by itself.Battle System:Enemies do little to no damage and spend half their turns defending and just dragging the battle out, one mob does about 20 damage when it attacks yet when it poisons a character they take 100+ damage a turn. Oh yeah, your characters start out with an absurd amount of health and level up at an insane rate despite killing the exact same weak enemies. Your main character does around 100 damage with his standard attack, the enemies you encounter at the start have about that much health. The kicker? Your characters do not actually have any weapons equipped when you get them, not even a basic rusty sword or anything which is just plain lazy and makes me wonder what in the hell are they infusing when they use weapon enhancement abilities? The majority of the ablities are lazy renamings (your non-clone clone jutsu also has thunder clone, fire clone, etc. variations) and have animations that don't match them at all. Based on the clips provided on the steam page it appears that even later in the game the damage values barely change if at all.Pros:+ If you don't know anything about Naruto then you might have some funCons:- Storyline is a bland blatant rip off of one of the more popular manga's (Naruto)- Generic Soundtrack straight from RPG Maker- Battle system is boring and unbalanced- Dialogue is extremely poor and vulgar and full of grammatical errors that create and unimmersive experience- Littered with glitchesTL;DR:2/10I always strive to give games a chance, even the indie developers and the RPG Maker games that playeres produce, but this is among the few games you should avoid even if it's a few dollars."
