76561197972252663,Not Recommended,399790,18943577,"Posted: 7 November, 2015",all,[G]Manlove,"The makers of this game think best part of jrpgs is combat, which is always the worst part. Endlessly repeating the same things (skills, combos etc) over and over again. Even worse, this game has unseen enemy encounters with those that you can see. Which is pretty idiotic. At some point of the game even normal enemies start to have so much hp that random encounters vs normal enemies last for minutes. And you have to fight them ... a lot. Also 90% of the skills are completely useless. And with enemy hp so high even your best skills dont do enough damage. And at some point enemies will start to stunlock your whole party forever.Also that genius who thought its a good idea that enemies can spawn from treasure chests should never make games again. Also the other thing about combat later is that only your skills that use TP[TP is another mana, only worse] do any damage. And of those only those that use all your TP (100) at one time. So combat turns into use a potion to get 100 tp, use skill, use potion to get 100 tp etc etc, and the best part is that those skills can even miss, losing all your TP.Also there is no use fighting after one point, because enemies scale with your level. So everytime a random encounter starts you can try to run away, except from chest and visible monster (what the hell?). Most of the time the running away doensnt work and because you cant access menu or load in combat forces you to close the game and when you have to do this all the time, it really buggers your steam friends receiving constant notions that you are playing this awful game. The story is pretty nice (in a so bad dialogue it turns kinda into good way), Naw who am I kidding its bad as hell.And nothing can save it as the abyssmal combat ruins the game.And the last thing, I've never ever wished that game would end more. But no it just keeps going and going, and splitting the party all the time forcing you with horrible party combinations and with less people easier for enemies to stunlock you to death. Theres lots of content that should have been scrapped and even cheap things like big maps with mazes and levers(are there just to make the game longer) that you need to push in correct order which you cant see as theres no map and view distance is too near. All while trying to avoid combat from invisible & visible enemies and saving everytime you open a chest, because if theres combat, you need to restart the game.Example battle I might never win. 5 Enemies vs 1 my hero. They use 3 different stuns (stun, paralyze and ice) If any of them stun me, combat is automatically lost. You can only protect yourself vs stuns with armors that have worse stats and only protect vs 1 effect so no dice there. If I luck through one enemy turn without stunlock, I can use 1 spell, which is my best spell and it does about 500-600 damage, enemies have about 10k-15k health.So 1/10 avoid like the plague."
