,Not Recommended,399790,22771646,"Posted: 2 May, 2016",all,stardustsunday,"Everything wrong with this game can be summarised in one sentence:Extremely $hitty battle system.It's not obvious in the beginning, but once you level up to 20-something, the absolute r3tardedness of it all becomes clear.Some examples of what I mean:1) At level 27, ceteris paribus (i.e. all conditions being equal), your normal attack is 61, versus your enemy's normal attack of 519. This is with the best available gear and maximum power-ups in the form of various item purchases.2) The elemental attacks are frigging meaningless - e.g. you would think a ""flaming rat"" would be immune to fire right? And yes, forsomefire attacks they get very little damage. But for a few fire attacks, they receive the same damage as others, and can also suffer from the ""+burn"" status effect - even though the graphics clearly depict them as being already on fire (and their element is fire)! Where's the logic?!3) At the ninja tournament, you are suddenly made to use characters youwere not using on a regular basis before. (The game always forcefully assigns characters to you to fight with throughout.) As a result, because these characters were not prepped or appropriately levelled up for the challenge, it is nigh impossible to win the battle using them. You have to be popping +HP pills all the time, and even then it's a huge challenge (you just have to betting on the fact that your opponent won't kill you using one of their specials, which have the potential to wipe you out at one go, since your opponents are several levels higher than you are, and equipped with the best possible gear!!!). Where's the fun in that???4) Normal attacks, which consume no MP and TP, deal WAY more damage than magic/skill attacks. I'm talking figures like 448 (using normal attack) as opposed to 92 (using MP/TP attack). Get lost!!!!!!5) You never ever get a chance to remove status effects like +poison, +blind, +burn, etc because some of your enemies are so fast that their turn keeps coming before you even get a chance to move. This in particular happens during the ninja tournament. So, just wait to die. Kthx.I suspect most of the these problems have to do with the fact that, after you reach a certain level, the game just suddenly starts assigning you enemies that are at least 2-3 levels higher than you. So when you're at level 27 for instance, you could be facing 6 enemies at levels 28, 27, 29, 29, 25, 28 respectively. And yes, it's YOU (one person), versus 6 of them. What the hell.It's a pity because I kind of enjoyed the game in the earlier stages, before it started going completely insane with the battle system. The story was corny, but the narrative and goals were clear, and there were many places and items to explore. (Speaking of which, some of the items were bleedin' USELESS. Once again, you'll only find this out later on in the game when more items start becoming available, and you realise they are 100% redundant. Youcan't even usemany of them during battle. Shan't elaborate because my consternation at this game is growing with every word I type.)So, yeah. I basically wasted my time going this far in this game, because I've concluded that it'simpossibleto proceed without some extreme hair-tearing and head-banging (against the wall or table) due to the anger and frustration that this game's battle system will induce in you.I should also mention that the English is beyond atrocious. E.g. ""insensitive"" used instead of ""incentive""; ""peak"" used instead of ""pique"", and so on. And you get spellings like ""rouge"" (instead of ""rogue"" - and the wrongly-spelled version appears for the WHOLE game!!!), ""paralized"" (instead of ""paralysed""), etc etc. Very often, the words are spelled likehow the game author thinks they are pronounced, instead of what they actually are. He could probably write his own dictionary with the sheer number of words he's re-spelled.And then there's the dialogue - in the beginning of the game it's still quite ok, then suddenly, you start seeing ""f***"" appeareverywhere.*shakes head*Forget it. Just forget it."
