76561198209225232,Not Recommended,399790,20287869,"Posted: 4 January, 2016",all,crazydicelady,"TL;DRBased on Naruto, not inspired by Chrono Trigger/Final Fantasy/Dragon Warrior.It's okay, just know what you're getting into.3/10Would Not RecommendFirst things first: This is not the worst game I've ever played.That being said, I can't recommend this game. The game came in a bundle with a few other games for practically pennies to the dollar, so I didn't read into the reviews before purchasing it.That was a mistake on my part. Always read the reviews.At first, I didn't know what to think of this game. For the first 10-20 minutes or so, I thought it might be a parody game, something meant to be silly. This is because although the description called the game ""heavily inspired by Chrono Trigger, Final Fantasy VI, and the Dragon Quest series,"" the only series that it is remotely similar to is Naruto. Actually, the game reads like a confusing Naruto fanfiction: it mashes together Eastern-ish and Western themes to the point where its almost funny (your Village's Leader in the about? His name was Kage Alex) and there are a few rediculous moments in the dialouge (CHAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA-), and I think the game could have been hilarious.The battle mechanics are unbalanced and weird, and though I leveled up at an absurd rate, battles still dragged on to the point of being tedious. To be honest, I only got about 2 hours into this ""12 hour RPG"" and I had to put it down. The problem was that it just got so repetitive that I completely lost interest, and any investment I might have had in the plot went out the window.However, I think this game should have been what it feels like it is: A Naruto fan game. I would have enjoyed playing a Naruto RPG, even just for the novelty of it. But they dropped some really big, heavy names in the description, where the only things they have in common in this game are being pixelated turn-based RPGs.I know this game must have taken a lot of time and effort, and I would hate to see something I spent so much time and effort on be torn apart in the reviews. But my biggest problem with it is that the game's description and About were... misleading. I felt a little tricked, and no matter how little I spend on something I do not want to feel like I'd been fooled into doing it.I may pick it up later after getting a chance to digest it more, but as of right now I doubt it."
