76561198347859269,Recommended,399790,28480336,"Posted: 19 December, 2016",all,Save Our Souls,"Destiny Warriors is an epic 12 hour JRPG inspired by the greats on Super Nintendo, Sega MegaDrive (Genesis), and the Turbo Duo.Thirteen years ago, your village's leader set off to confront the spirit beasts that threatened to invade and destroy your home.Among these spirit beasts was a fire dragon that burned everything to ashes, a sea serpent with great healing abilities and a lightning bird that could attack faster than light itself. While the village leader was a powerful warrior, trained in both hand-to-hand combat and magic, he could not overpower them.Ultimately, he had no choice but to sacrifice his own life by casting a powerful sealing spell on the beasts. This trapped the beasts in the souls of three human children. Unfortunately no one in the village, including the children themselves, knew which children's souls contained the trapped spirit beasts.Thirteen years later, as you enter the village's elite warrior academy, the spirit beasts have become restless and threaten to break free from their hosts. As student after student goes missing, it's up to you and three friends to abandon your training and set out into the unknown world. Use magic, might, and cunning in order to find the missing students and defeat the spirit beasts in this amazing JRPG."
,Recommended,399790,32365702,Posted: 12 June,all,YPRPG,"This game provides many hours of fun - the main campaign is well over 10 hours, without knowing the exact length; but due to the difficulty of some of the later levels, you might not have the willpower to see it through to the end.The story is engaging, as every completed mission brings a new development to the plot, and additional dialogue between the characters. It genuinely feels like the quests are there to accommodate the plot, and not the other way around, which is above what most RPGs offer in that area. There are over a dozen characters, six of which are generally your party members, and they each have interesting personalities and side issues, such as rivalries and romance.There is a nice variety in the types of missions, but they most commonly consist of travelling through a maze of treasure-filled pathways with random encounters, until you reach the area with the main boss. Battles run long, even the less important ones, and you frequently must use multiple items to replenish your stats.Exploration is limited to wandering the town, visiting shops, and speaking to locals who occasionally have something new to say, or some special item to give you.There is a huge diversity of items to buy at the shop, and you usually have lots of money to spend. It is likely you'll need a lot of stuff for battles, but unfortunately, it is impossible to predict which items will be useful on your next mission.The hitch of this game is that some missions are very difficult, and virtually impossible to beat unless you have the right items, and/or equipment. Often in these cases, the only thing to do is to go back to a previous save, lose up to an hour of progress, and buy the items necessary. If you don't have a previous save, you're simply out of luck.Overall, this is a great game, in terms of both story and combat, but if you are intent on game completion, either remember to save often, or give the game a pass."
