,Not Recommended,399790,21156252,"Posted: 12 February, 2016",all,*Logan*,"This is a terrible turn-based RPG made with the RPG Maker engine and it's one of the worst games I've played.I can get past the limited options and visual settings that RPG Maker games suffer from, and I can get past the generic artwork and horrible music, but this game has a horrible combat system and that I can NOT get past.My main issue with this game is the fact that your enemies level up with you.This is rarely used in RPGs and with good reason. It's a horrible idea that makes no sense, and makes you want to either:1. AVOID battles at all costs to keep the enemies low level or2. Fight in the same area leveling up to 99.However, WHY would you want to skip battles in an RPG? Why would you want to repeat the same areas if you don't gain an advantage from grinding?Why do the enemies level up between battles? My team hit level 10 in the first area and the same slimes and flowers were level 10 as well. It's not like they were fighting battles, and this doesn't make sense because in the first area of the game you should not have to be fighting such high level creatures.I'm not saying this is difficult, I'm saying this is not fun and that's the most important thing.This game is garbage for this reason, and I would suggest avoiding it no matter how cheap it goes on sale.Edit: I've learned that it's possible things change later in the game, but based on this being the introduction to the game, I didn't want to continue. This is a very bad way to start off an RPG."
