76561198160768382,Not Recommended,399790,23014093,"Posted: 15 May, 2016",all,ac_editing,"-Some spoilers ahead, you are warned-At first I loved this game. I was definitely a Naruto rip off, but there were quirks and commentary that made it humorous. (Spark will forever be known as Dude Elf to me thanks to looking like an elf, and the first dialogue coming out of him including ""dude"") The different types of skills and weapons made for an interesting game play, and it was relatively easy to level up. I was confused when Max suddenly capped, but figured he was the Sasuke character and would be lost eventually. Overall though, not that bad.Then the ninja tournament came. Suddenly the battle system became a joke. The status effects and speed of the opponents was so ridiculous that I had to redo the first battle at least 20 times. Things only went downhill from there. The enemies, especially boss fights, were ridiculous. Enemy defense was so high that attacks that used to do hundreds or even thousands of damage were now doing 1. When the beast modes finally showed up...wow that was a let down. Rather than power up during beast modes, character skills were limited and the bosses in particular seemed to be exceptionally strong and fast.I will give an example: in the first temple, you are forced to fight clones of your current party plus the phantom summoning them. Round one was pretty balanced. They had my attacks, I had theirs, so just working out how to attack them so that I came out on top was both easy and straight forward. Then round 2 happened. The characters are forced into beast mode while more clones pop up. Suddenly my characters were down to less techniques than I could count on a hand. That's nice and all, except they are dishing out attacks that both freeze and take out half the hp of the characters (keep in mind my characters are both capped, wearing their strongest armors, and have items equipped to add to their power and defense.). What happens when I dish out the same technique which my character happened to keep? 1hp damage. Compared to thousands on their part. I'm sorry, but what? Add on the fact that these guys have status effects, are insanely fast, and have both a healer and a phantom which can resummon clones in a turn, and it was something worth rage quitting over.Now I am at the second temple, and already there are lizardmen who are showing the same ridiculous effect spam and healing techniques. Let's also include here that they are pretty high in level, which would put them on par with the main guy on the team, but the game has forcefully pair him up with his ten levels lower father (which the game says can equip armor and a weapon...which he cannot), and a character who is lvl literally 28 levels lower.I haven't even finished the game yet, but this is one that I'm seriously considering just letting sit unfinished."
