76561197991137557,Recommended,399790,34462989,Posted: 24 August,all,BrianHammerhand,"This is a fun little RPG to pass the time. Bottom line, it's enjoyable if a bit amateurish in spots and inexplicable in others (why are the forests littered with chests just waiting to be opened?) Yes the dialogue is a bit juvenile and heavily-inspired by Naruto but its not a direct rip-off. No more so than the dozens of Chrono Trigger or Final Fantasy inspired games are rip offs of those series. Instead of knights and kings you have ninjas and kages (and yes, some other very Naruto-like elements).  Some weird mixing of words that sound more like Chinese than Japanese are also in the game like ""X-tu"". So if you are tired of the standard western knights and dragons in your JRPG then this is a nice change. The gameplay is fun without endless exploration of mazes and excessive doubling back or random foes as seen in some other similar inexpensive RPG maker titles. The story progresses well without too much time in dialogue or too much time in random combat. The difficulty level is fine for a casual JRPG and I would even boost it for a challenge. I did not feel that the generic RPG maker tiles or artwork detracted from the game - they seemed suitable to me, but I have not played others that use these particular graphics. One downside as I see it is that some of the powers the characters develop far too quickly and just out of the blue in the wilderness. I would have preferred to see them develop these skills by training them in the village and practicing with them, than getting a Monte Haul of skills."
76561198322377265,Recommended,399790,34316405,Posted: 17 August,all,SamuraiXBrother,"Despite all the reviews here saying this game is terrible, let me tell ou that no, it isn't.The plot is fairly simple, but there are no stupid holes or things that make no sense, so it keeps you going.Now ofcourse, this is an RPG maker game, and it really shows with it's menu's and such, and to be honest, I'm not sure if it's worth the 1 Dollar. There are a lot more RPG maker games online... for free.I still really enjoyed it and it has the item and menu system that you expect from an RPG maker game.However, it does have one thing that I don't see to often in RPG maker games:The battles play out in a Final Fantasy sorta way. You see your team on the right, and the enemy's on the left. The health bars and menus in combat are quite nice and it isn't all that confusing.Sometimes enemy's will attack before you even get a opotunity to attack, and overall this game kinda felt like the SNES Final Fantasy's in a way. And the game has some nice customisebility(sorry for terrible english there).The character's aren't anything special, and they curse a bit to often that it looks like overkill, and kinda ruins the flow.They do all have different atributes though, like one is very powerfull in ATK but pretty slow, one is fast with medium attack and a bit more luck then others. The other is the typical healer that can deal quite some water damage.And one is the Emo (I'm not joking) with some status moves and in a way is kinda like the Black Mage form FF.Oh, and they're all ninja's. No idea why. They don't look like ninja's, use magic and I found myself ignoreing it.In the end, this game is pretty basic, but if you think you like the other games in the bundle (wich I would say is the way to buy this game), then buy it. I really enjoyed my time with this game. Altough I still need to play the other 3 RPG's in the bundle.Hope this review helped you!"
